wikipedia_page.main: Edward Liddle (27 May 1878 – 22 November 1968) (sometimes Liddell) was an English football player, manager and scout. He played in the Football League for Gainsborough Trinity, Clapton Orient, with whom he spent the majority of his playing career, and Arsenal, and spent time with a number of other clubs at varying levels. Liddle went on to manage four teams – Southend United, Queens Park Rangers, Fulham and Luton Town – in league football.
